---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'What Would You Teach? · The Second Design',
  description: 'You have a way of thinking that most students never get access to. We know how to make it teachable.',
  robots: { index: false, follow: false },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
  ============================================================ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 pt-24 pb-24">

    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-1/3 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-violet-500/10 rounded-full blur-[120px]"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/4 w-[300px] h-[300px] bg-emerald-500/8 rounded-full blur-[100px]"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative container max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">

      <!-- Back link -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-10">
        <a href="/real-world-ready" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500 hover:text-violet-400 transition-colors">
          ← Real World Ready
        </a>
        <span class="text-slate-700">·</span>
        <a href="/real-world-ready/donate" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500 hover:text-violet-400 transition-colors">
          Support Us →
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-400 mb-10">The Second Design · Real World Ready</p>

      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white leading-[1.05] mb-8">
        What would<br />
        <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-400 via-blue-400 to-emerald-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          you teach?
        </span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        You have a way of thinking that most students never get access to. We know how to make it teachable.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       BODY
  ============================================================ -->
  <div class="bg-slate-950">
    <div class="container max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pb-28 space-y-20">

      <!-- The observation -->
      <section>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="h-px w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-500 to-blue-500"></div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-400">The observation</span>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-5">
          The people who've built something real have a framework in their head they've never named. A principle they apply instinctively. A way of approaching risk, failure, timing, decisions that isn't obvious until someone points it out.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          That thinking rarely reaches students. Not because it's inaccessible. Because nobody's built the bridge.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- We build the bridge -->
      <section>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="h-px w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-emerald-500"></div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-blue-400">What we do</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">We build the bridge.</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-5">
          Real World Ready takes one idea and turns it into a 90-minute session. Not a talk. Not a panel. A structured, facilitated experience where students work through that idea, apply it to something real in their own lives, and leave with something concrete.
        </p>

        <!-- Example callout -->
        <div class="my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.04] border border-white/10">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500 mb-3">For example</p>
          <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We took the idea of a Shitty First Draft: the principle that your first attempt doesn't need to be good, it just needs to exist. We built a 90-minute session around it. Students ship a draft in the room. <span class="text-white font-semibold">Average rating: 9.5 out of 10.</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          We've done this with agency, with system thinking, with navigating uncertainty without a plan. Each one started as a concept someone had already internalized. We asked the right questions, built the session, and tested it until it worked.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Pull quote -->
      <div class="border-l-4 border-violet-500 pl-6 py-2">
        <p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white leading-snug">
          Your thinking, made permanent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- The invitation -->
      <section>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="h-px w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-violet-500"></div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-400">The invitation</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">One conversation.</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-5">
          Tell us what you'd want a 20-year-old to know. A framework you rely on. A principle you wish you'd learned earlier. A way of thinking that changed how you operate.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          We'll take it from there. If it's the right fit, we design a session around it, pilot it with students, and run it many times across campuses and cohorts for years.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- What this looks like -->
      <section>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
          <div class="h-px w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-500 to-blue-500"></div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-400">What this looks like</span>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { n: "01", title: "A 45-minute conversation", desc: "You talk, we listen, we ask questions. That's all we need." },
            { n: "02", title: "We build the session", desc: "A structure, a workbook, a facilitation guide, all designed around the idea you shared." },
            { n: "03", title: "You see what we made", desc: "Attend a pilot session if you want, or just watch a recording. Either way, you'll see your thinking in action." },
            { n: "04", title: "It reaches students", desc: "Initially through TinkerHub's 85+ campus chapters across India, and wherever else Real World Ready runs." },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/10">
              <span class="text-lg font-bold font-mono text-violet-400/40 shrink-0 leading-none mt-0.5">{item.n}</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-white mb-1">{item.title}</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <section class="pt-4 border-t border-white/10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">If this sounds worth a conversation.</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Write to Gautham directly. No form, no deck, no pitch. Just tell him what you're thinking.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-base">
          <li>
            <a href="mailto:gautham@theseconddesign.com" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-white transition-colors">
              gautham@theseconddesign.com
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://wa.me/9400474785" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">
              WhatsApp →
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
